{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1782424216,"nonce":"F7+hw/jPicLutIRsT2w79FjlhC8=","message":"Shipped in PR #49 (squash 7d17c83). Re-added second support with uniform PostgreSQL/MySQL semantics:\n\n- extract(DateField::Second, ts) -\u003e i64: whole-seconds component, floored (CAST(FLOOR(EXTRACT(SECOND FROM ts)) AS bigint/SIGNED); FLOOR is a no-op on MySQL's integer).\n- extract_second(ts) -\u003e f64: fractional seconds. PG CAST(EXTRACT(SECOND FROM ts) AS double precision); MySQL CAST(EXTRACT(SECOND_MICROSECOND FROM ts) / 1000000.0 AS DOUBLE) via a new Dialect::extract_second_uses_microsecond_unit hook (operand referenced once, so a literal/param is a single placeholder).\n\nFull stack: ExtractSecondExprAst + extract_second + visit_extract_second, ExprNode::ExtractSecond IR, view_render + KDL; re-added Second DateField (also enables date_trunc('second', ...)). Seconds are timezone-invariant, so no _at variant. Tests across all backends + a PG integration round-trip (56 / 56.789). CI green; Codex clean.\n\nMillisecond/Microsecond fields remain deferred (PG and MySQL semantics diverge — no uniform mapping yet).\n\nClosing.","files":null}]}